<paragraph id="99313682FA74D427FF2B5DC0AEB8FA8D" blockId="2.[166,747,1256,1283]" box="[166,747,1256,1283]" pageId="2" pageNumber="53">
<heading id="C27981EEFA74D427FF2B5DC0AEB8FA8D" box="[166,747,1256,1283]" fontSize="36" level="2" pageId="2" pageNumber="53" reason="3">
<taxonomicName id="5E8E4D01FA74D427FF2B5DC0AE3FFA8D" authority="(Strobl, 1873)" baseAuthorityName="Strobl" baseAuthorityYear="1893" box="[166,620,1256,1283]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Ophiomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aeneonitens">
<emphasis id="ABFAEA90FA74D427FF2B5DC0AD97FA8D" bold="true" box="[166,452,1256,1283]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="53">Ophiomyia aeneonitens</emphasis>
(Strobl, 1873)
</taxonomicName>
(fig. 5–11)
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="99313682FA74D427FF565C09AFF2FAB9" blockId="2.[219,929,1313,1336]" box="[219,929,1313,1336]" pageId="2" pageNumber="53">
M a t e r i a l e x a m i n e d. Near Krasnoye, chalk hills, 
<date id="ED301042FA74D427FD525C09AF1AFAB9" box="[735,841,1313,1335]" pageId="2" pageNumber="53" value="2012-05-23">23.05.2012</date>
, 5 ♂, 
<specimenCount id="8F88FD0BFA74D427FCF15C09AFCFFAB6" box="[892,924,1313,1336]" pageId="2" pageNumber="53" type="female">1 ♀</specimenCount>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D1946509FA74D426FF565C71A89EFD5F" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="54" pageId="2" pageNumber="53" type="description">
<paragraph id="99313682FA74D427FF565C71AF39FA7D" blockId="2.[166,1225,1368,1843]" pageId="2" pageNumber="53">
R e d e s c r i p t i o n. Head (fig. 5, 6, 9). Orbit slightly projected above eye in profile; 2 orb s, 2 fr s; frorb sta reclinate, short, sparse; facial bulb 0.8× as wide as pedicel, slightly widening ventrally, with wide, shallow furrow at level of antennal base; lunule rounded; vibrissa present in both sexes; maximal height of eye 12.5 
<emphasis id="ABFAEA90FA74D427FCCF5C91AF00FA5D" bold="true" box="[834,851,1465,1491]" pageId="2" pageNumber="53">×</emphasis>
maximal height of gena; ocellar triangle reaching level of 1st orb s; 1st flagellomere rounded.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="99313682FA74D427FF565CD1A870F9DD" blockId="2.[166,1225,1368,1843]" pageId="2" pageNumber="53">
Wing. Costa reaching just beyond apex of R 
<subScript id="050A34C7FA74D427FD545F23AEA0F997" attach="right" box="[729,755,1547,1561]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="53">4+5</subScript>
; calypter and fringe beige in male, white in female; margin beige. Wing veins white with costal and radial veins beige basally and darker apically. Crossvein r-m lacking. Wing white. Length of wing 1.7 mm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="99313682FA74D427FF565F71AE4AF91D" blockId="2.[166,1225,1368,1843]" pageId="2" pageNumber="53">Mesonotum black, shining (anterior view); 2 dc; ac 2 nearest to sctsctl sut and 6 at level of 2nd dc; halter and legs black.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="99313682FA74D427FF565FB1AD55F8BD" blockId="2.[166,1225,1368,1843]" pageId="2" pageNumber="53">
Male genitalia (fig. 7, 8). Phallus 0.33 mm long, its shape atypical for 
<taxonomicName id="5E8E4D01FA74D427FB895FB1A8D5F93D" authorityName="Braschnikov" authorityYear="1897" box="[1028,1158,1689,1715]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Ophiomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="ABFAEA90FA74D427FB895FB1A8D5F93D" box="[1028,1158,1689,1715]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="53">Ophiomyia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, having a short, wide, H-shaped basiphallus, a wide endophallus that is strongly projected above the distal margin of the distiphallus and reaching the distal margins of the basiphallus, and the proximal parts of the distiphallus are quite wide with the apex narrow and strongly tapered.
</paragraph>
<caption id="CDF1660AFA75D426FF235891AEEBFE64" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452824" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6452824" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452824/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" startId="3.[174,207,441,463]" targetBox="[177,1231,174,433]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph id="99313682FA75D426FF235891AEEBFE64" blockId="3.[174,1232,441,490]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">
Fig. 12–17. 
<taxonomicName id="5E8E4D01FA75D426FE925892AD8CFE41" authority="(Hendel)" baseAuthorityName="Hendel" baseAuthorityYear="1923" box="[287,479,441,463]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Ophiomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beckeri">
<emphasis id="ABFAEA90FA75D426FE925892AD2CFE40" box="[287,383,441,463]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">O. beckeri</emphasis>
(Hendel)
</taxonomicName>
: 12, 13 — male head; 14 — phallus, lateral view; 15 — female head; 16 — egg guide, left blade; 17 — spermatheca. Scale bar 0.1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="99313682FA75D426FF2358D7A872FDA1" blockId="3.[174,1233,511,559]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">
Рис. 12–17. 
<taxonomicName id="5E8E4D01FA75D426FEAC58D7AD8EFD9B" authority="(Hendel)" baseAuthorityName="Hendel" baseAuthorityYear="1923" box="[289,477,511,533]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Ophiomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beckeri">
<emphasis id="ABFAEA90FA75D426FEAC58D7AD2CFD9A" box="[289,383,511,532]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">O. beckeri</emphasis>
(Hendel)
</taxonomicName>
: 12, 13 — голова самца; 14 — фаллюс, латеральный вид; 15 — голова самки; 16 — левая лопасть восьмого стернита; 17 — сперматека. Масштабная линейка 0,1 мм.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="99313682FA75D426FF525B7EA830FD3E" blockId="3.[170,1229,598,721]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Female terminalia (fig. 10, 11). Both spermathecae equal, spherical, with narrow, subcylindrical, collar-like base. Proximal and ventral margins of egg guide with minute, posteriorly directed teeth. Membrane of medial margin with several sparse dark scales.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="99313682FA75D426FF525B9FA89EFD5F" blockId="3.[170,1229,598,721]" box="[223,1229,694,721]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">
D i s t r i b u t i o n. 
<collectingCountry id="E1997612FA75D426FE235B9EAE52FD5E" box="[430,513,694,720]" name="Austria" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Austria</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="FD1F4B73FA75D426FD815B9EAEF7FD5F" author="Hendel, F." box="[524,676,694,721]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" pagination="129 - 192" refId="ref13393" refString="Hendel, F. 59. Agromyzidae [part 3] // Die Fliegen der palaearktische Region / Ed. E. Lindner. - 1931. - Bd. 6 (1), Lfg. 56. - S. 129 - 192." type="book chapter" year="1931">Hendel, 1931</bibRefCitation>
